&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ST GEORGE&#39;S UNIVERSITY HOSPITALS NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ST GEORGE’S HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Thoracic Surgery &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10 PAs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the above post based at St Georges Hospital, South West London. The successful applicant would join a team of Thoracic Surgeons based at St Georges providing Thoracic services. The post is for 10 PAs per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new appointment within the Thoracic Surgery department, and we are seeking a full-time consultant with expertise in all aspects of thoracic surgery. As a member of a multidisciplinary team, the post holder will work in collaboration with the existing consultant team to deliver high quality patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to undertake a variety of Thoracic operations, such as keyhole thoracic surgery (video assisted thoracoscopic surgery) and surgery for lung cancer. Ideally the post holder should hold a further degree (PhD) and have an interest and experience of Robotic Thoracic Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to a clinical workload at St Georges, the unit provides input to Epsom &amp; St Helier, East Surrey, Kingston, Croydon, Royal Surrey, St Peter’s &amp; Ashford, Royal Marsden, and St Richards (Chichester) for clinic activity and MDT’s. The post holder will play a key role in the fulfillment of these requirements with district hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is based in the Atkinson Morley Wing of St Georges University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and is available to be taken up as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enquiries about the post may be directed to Ms. Carol Tan (Care Group Lead) on 020 8725 3287.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
